Instructions: Creating the "Secret Santa" Program

Step 1: Installing Python
      1. Go to python.org/downloads.
      2. Download and install the latest version of Python for your operating system (Windows, macOS, or Linux). Make sure to check the option "Add Python to PATH" during installation.

Step 2: Installing Required Libraries:

Open your command prompt or terminal and type the following commands:

      Copy code:
          pip install tk
      
      Copy code:
          pip install random
      
      Copy code:
          pip install messagebox

Step 3: Downloading and Running the Script
      1. Copy the entire code of the program provided to you.
      2. Open Notepad or any other simple text editing application.
      3. Paste the copied code into the new document.
      4. Save the file with a .py extension, for example, SecretSanta.py. Remember to choose "All Files" as the file type when saving.
      5. Run the script by double-clicking on the SecretSanta.py file.

Step 4: Using the Program
      1. After running, a window with a graphical interface will appear.
      2. Enter the names of the participants in the text field and click "Add".
      3. Once you've added all the names, you can click "Draw" to conduct the drawing.
      4. The program will inform you about who was drawn for whom. Make sure no one is peeking at your computerized drawing!
      5. After finishing, there will be a message indicating that all drawings have been completed.

Note:
This program is created for entertainment purposes. Make sure participants are aware of the game and do not use it in a way that violates the law or makes others uncomfortable.

